## `<file-level: imports>`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-flock-1 -->

### Purpose
Tests for file locking across FUSE — the three advisory flavors, exercised by two subprocess clients so the kernel-VFS side of the semantics is covered. Without this file, the library's `locks.py` could pass all its unit tests and still be broken end-to-end because pyfuse3's lock callbacks (`getlk`/`setlk`/`setlkw`/`flock`) must be wired correctly.

All tests `<!-- trace: skipped -->` — syscall boundary + subprocess.

### Implementation Notes

```python
import errno
import fcntl
import os
import struct
import subprocess
import sys
import textwrap
import pytest

pytestmark = pytest.mark.fuse


def _worker(py: str) -> subprocess.Popen:
    """Spawn a subprocess running the given python code via -c."""
    return subprocess.Popen(
        [sys.executable, "-c", textwrap.dedent(py)],
        stdin=subprocess.PIPE, stdout=subprocess.PIPE,
        stderr=subprocess.PIPE, text=False,
    )
```

