## `test_fuse_flock_exclusive_blocks_second(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-flock-2 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary + subprocess -->

### Postconditions

```python
path = mount / "locked"
path.write_bytes(b"x")

# First process takes exclusive flock; second sees EWOULDBLOCK.
p1 = _worker(f"""
    import fcntl, time
    f = open({str(path)!r}, 'rb+')
    fcntl.flock(f, fcntl.LOCK_EX)
    print('LOCKED', flush=True)
    time.sleep(10)
""")
assert p1.stdout.readline().strip() == b"LOCKED"

with open(path, "rb+") as f:
    with pytest.raises(BlockingIOError) as e:
        fcntl.flock(f, fcntl.LOCK_EX | fcntl.LOCK_NB)
    assert e.value.errno in (errno.EWOULDBLOCK, errno.EAGAIN)

p1.kill()
p1.wait()
```

