## `test_fuse_flock_shared_coexists(mount)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-flock-3 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: syscall boundary + subprocess -->

### Postconditions

```python
path = mount / "shared"
path.write_bytes(b"x")

p1 = _worker(f"""
    import fcntl, time
    f = open({str(path)!r}, 'rb')
    fcntl.flock(f, fcntl.LOCK_SH)
    print('SH1', flush=True)
    time.sleep(10)
""")
assert p1.stdout.readline().strip() == b"SH1"

# Second shared from this process should succeed.
with open(path, "rb") as f:
    fcntl.flock(f, fcntl.LOCK_SH | fcntl.LOCK_NB)   # no error
    fcntl.flock(f, fcntl.LOCK_UN)

p1.kill()
p1.wait()
```

